Currently, it is not possible to create Query Rules that dynamically filter search results based on user input from the search box. The inability to utilize regular expressions to extract values such as "less than XX," "greater than XX," or "under XXg " from search terms and employ them as variables ($1) in Query Rules to set conditions like "$lt: $1" poses a limitation. Despite attempts to specify rules like the one below, they cannot be saved:



{noformat}{
  "criteria": {
    "searchTermMatchesRegex": ".*less than (\d+) min.*"
  },
  "actions": [
    {
      "actionType": "ADD_FILTER",
      "filter": {
        "c_cook_time_number": {
          "$lt": $1
        }
      },
      "verticals": [
        "recipe"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "name": "Less than X min"
}
{noformat}
